    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.7.0-dev+1292-ge9b53f3fb\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch Linux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.24.4\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n1. Run `nvim --clean`\r\n2. Type `:call nvim_open_win(0, v:false, #{ width: 10, height: 10, relative: \"editor\", row: 10, col: 10 })` and press Enter\r\n3. Type `:unhide 1` and press Enter\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNo crash or hang\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n`:unhide 1` leads to a hang with `E444: Cannot close last window` spammed in messages.",
